cast.overview: An adaptation of the successful stage musical based on Victor Hugo's classic novel set in 19th-century France. Jean Valjean, a man imprisoned for stealing bread, must flee a relentless policeman named Javert. The pursuit consumes both men's lives, and soon Valjean finds himself in the midst of the student revolutions in France.
cast.title: Les Misérables

cast.overview: When the denizens of Littlehampton – including conservative Edith – begin receiving letters full of hilarious profanities, rowdy Irish migrant Rose is charged with the crime. Suspecting something amiss, the town's women band together to investigate.
cast.title: Wicked Little Letters

cast.original_title: Mamma Mia! Here We Go Again
cast.overview: Five years after meeting her three fathers, Sophie Sheridan prepares to open her mother’s hotel. In 1979, young Donna Sheridan meets the men who each could be Sophie’s biological father.
cast.title: Mamma Mia! Here We Go Again

details.biography: Hugh William Skinner (born 6 January 1985) is a British actor. He is best known for starring in television shows W1A (2014–2017), The Windsors (2016–present) and The Witcher (2023), and his appearances in musical films Les Misérables (2012) and Mamma Mia! Here We Go Again (2018).
details.name: Hugh Skinner
